# Deployment Implementation Plan

## Goal
To successfully deploy the Skynex application to the public internet, we must decouple the codebase from local environments (`localhost`) and hardcoded secrets. We will prepare the code for standard PaaS (Platform as a Service) providers like Render (for backend) and Vercel (for frontend).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The database connection will temporarily still point to your local MySQL (`localhost`). When you deploy the backend online, you must provision an online MySQL database (e.g., using Aiven or Railway) and paste its URL into the backend's environment variables dashboard.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Updates
We need to configure the Flask app to use environment variables for sensitive data and ensure a production WSGI server is specified.

#### [MODIFY] [c:\skin\backend\app.py](file:///c:/skin/backend/app.py)
- Import `os` and `dotenv` to load a `.env` file if it exists.
- Replace `app.config['SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI'] = 'mysql+pymysql://root...'` with `os.getenv('DATABASE_URL', 'your_local_fallback')`.
- Replace `app.config['JWT_SECRET_KEY']` with `os.getenv('JWT_SECRET_KEY', 'dermai-super-secret')`.

#### [MODIFY] [c:\skin\backend\requirements.txt](file:///skin/backend/requirements.txt)
- Add `gunicorn` (production web server).
- Add `python-dotenv` (for local environment variables).

#### [NEW] `c:\skin\backend\Procfile`
- Add the line `web: gunicorn app:app` (standard Render/Heroku configuration).

### Frontend Updates
The frontend must dynamically point to the correct backend API depending on where it's running.

#### [NEW] `c:\skin\frontend\.env`
- Define `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000`.

#### [MODIFY] [c:\skin\frontend\src\App.jsx](file:///c:/skin/frontend/src/App.jsx)
- Replace all instances of `http://localhost:5000` with `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL`.

## Verification Plan
After these modifications, running `python app.py` and `npm run dev` locally will continue to work exactly as they do now, but the codebase will be 100% prepared to be pushed to GitHub and deployed by cloud providers. I will provide a dedicated Deployment Guide artifact outlining the exact platform steps once this code is ready.
